public class ProgramDom<T>
extends Dom<T>
implements ITask

Generic implementation of a program domain (a specialized kind of Java task).

A program domain maps each of N values of some related type in the given Java program (e.g., methods, types, statements of a certain kind, etc.) to a unique integer in the range [0..N-1]. The integers are assigned in the order in which the values are added to the domain.

Author:
Mayur Naik (mhn@cs.stanford.edu)
